<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<subsection xml:id="egagement" component="engagement">
  <title>Participation and Engagement</title>
  <p>
    Active participation is essential for success in this course.
Students are expected to engage consistently with the ALEKS learning system by watching instructional videos, reading the eText, and completing homework and learning activities. Because this is an asynchronous course, students are responsible for managing their time and making steady progress through the assigned ALEKS objectives.
  </p>
  <p>
Regular engagement with the course materials allows students to strengthen their understanding of the concepts and develop the problem-solving skills needed for success in future coursework. Students are encouraged to seek help when needed and to work consistently throughout the term rather than attempting to complete large portions of the work at once.
  </p>
</subsection>
